description: Deep Rose Pink. Large, semidouble with flared Golden stamens and wavy petals. Average, open growth. E. (Sasanqua x Reticulata). (U.S. 1988 - Nuccio’s).

name: Cambria
description: Rose Red. Very large, semidouble to loose peony form. Vigorous growth. E-M. (Reticulata seedling). (N.Z. 1978 - Clark).

name: Camellia City
description: Rose Red. Very large, semidouble. Average, upright growth. L. (Reticulata ‘Crimson Robe’ x Reticulata hybrid Jean Pursel’). (U.S. 1981 - Pursel).

name: Camelot
description: Rose Pink. Large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright, open growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Buddha’ seedling). (Aus. 1976 - Sebire).

name: Cameron Cooper
description: Vivid Pink. Large to very large, rose form double to peony form. Vigorous, upright, compact growth. E-L. (Reticulata ‘Cornelian’ x Japonica ‘Mrs. D. W. Davis.’). (U.S. 1976 - Pursel).

name: Carroll'S Legacy
description: Deep Pink with frosting with Yellow anthers and White filaments. Medium to large, semidouble form. Average, upright, medium density growth. M. (Seedling of Reticulata hybrid 'Frank Houser’). (U.S. 2023 - Mack McKinnon, Murrells Inlet, SC).

name: Dr. R. P. Mcdonald
description: Burgundy Red. Large, semidouble to peony form with crinkled petals. M-L. (Reticulata ‘Crimson Robe’ x Reticulata/ Japonica hybrid). (U.S. 1981 - Pursel).

name: Ed’S Red
description: Light Red with Reddish sheen. Large to very large, semidouble to rose form double. Average, upright, spreading growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Hulyn Smith’ seedling). (U.S. 1995 - E. Atkins, Shalimar, FL).

name: Eileen'S Smile
description: White with some Deep Pink freckles with Gold anthers and Creamy Yellow filaments. Large, semidouble form. Average, upright, open growth. E-M. (Seedling of Reticulata hybrid ‘Mouchang’). (U.S. 2021 - Pat B. Johnson, Cairo, GA).

name: Espana
description: Deep China Rose with White central petaloids. Very large, rose form double. Average, upright, compact growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Nuccio’s Ruby’ seedling). (U.S. 1987 - H. S. Hall, San Anselmo, CA).

name: Gilley’S Forever
description: Dark Pink with Golden anthers and White filaments. Large, semidouble. Average, upright, spreading growth. M-L. (Seedling of Reticulata hybrid 'Valley Knudsen’). (U.S. 2016 - Gilley).

name: Giorgio’S Pride
description: Dark Red. Large to very large, semidouble. Average growth. M-L. (Reticulata ‘Crimson Robe’ x Reticulata hybrid ‘Mary Stringfellow’). (U.S. 1984 - Pursel).

name: Henry’S Surprise
description: Deep Red. Very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright, open growth. M-L. (Reticulata ‘Chang’s Temple’ seedling). (N.Z. 1999 - H. B. McCounel).

name: Hulyn’S Meadowbrook
description: Medium Pink, sometimes frosted White with Gold anthers and White filaments; the bloom is often fluorescent. Very large, semidouble to full peony. Vigorous, upright, spreading growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Suzanne Withers’ x Reticulata hybrid ‘Frank Houser’). (U.S. 2014 - Hulyn Smith).

name: Hulyn’S Sweet Emily
description: Dark Pink with White anthers and Red filaments. Very large, peony form. Average, dense growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Hulyn Smith’ x Reticulata hybrid ‘Delta Dawn’). (U.S. 2010 - Hulyn Smith).

name: Im Pinkerton
description: Rose Red. Very large, peony form. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Buddha x [Reticulata ‘Crimson Robe’ x Lutchuensis]). (U.S. 1998 - Pursel).

name: Im Smelley
description: Dark Pink with bright Yellow anthers and White filaments. Very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright, open growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Curtain Call’ x Reticulata hybrid ‘Pleasant Memories’). (U.S. 2013 - James and Elaine Smelley, Moss Point, MS).

name: Ing Jing
description: See ‘Shining Jade’.

name: Inspiration
description: Phlox Pink. Medium, semidouble. (Reticulata x Saluenensis). (England 1954 - Hanger).

name: James Mccoy
description: Deep Burgundy Red. Large to very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (Reticulata ‘Crimson Robe’ x Reticulata/Saluenensis hybrid). (U.S. 1980 - Pursel).

name: Manaojuban
description: See ‘Cornelian Chrysanthemum Petal’.

name: Marjorie O’Malley
description: Rose Red. Large to very large, semidouble to loose peony form. M-L. (Reticulata ‘Crimson Robe’ x Reticulata hybrid Jean Pursel’). (U.S. 1982 - Pursel).

name: Mark’S Surprise
description: Deep Pink. Very large, peony form. Average growth. E-M. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Francie L.’ seedling). (Aus. 1984 - Sebire).

name: Mary O’Donnell
description: Orchid Pink. Medium to large, peony form to rose form double to formal double. Vigorous, dense, spreading, upright growth. E-L. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Lilette Whitman’ x Reticulata hybrid ‘Hulyn Smith’). (U.S. 1992 - Mandarich).

name: Nuccio’S Ruby
description: Very Dark Rich Red. Large to very large, semidouble with irregular, ruffled petals. Average, compact, upright growth. M. (Reticulata seedling). (U.S. 1974 - Nuccio’s). L, (Reticulata hybrid ‘Wild Form’ x Reticulata hybrid ‘Suzanne Withers’ x Nitidissima). (Aus. 2005 - Colleen Sherrington, Balwyn North, Vic.).

name: Satan’S Robe
description: Oriental Red. Large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (Hybrid ‘Satan’s Satin’ x Reticulata ‘Crimson Robe’). (U.S. 1965 - Feathers).

name: Susie O’Neill
description: Pale to medium Pink. Very large, anemone to loose peony form. Vigorous, open and upright growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid ‘Suzanne Withers’ x Reticulata hybrid Jean Pursel’). (Aus. 2002 - Dr. R. M. Withers, Donvale, Vic.).

name: Tony’S Joy
description: Bright Red. Large to very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (Reticulata x Japonica). (U.S. 1975 - A. Funari, Santa Clara, CA).

name: Udy Kerr
description: Light Pink. Large, formal double to rose form double. Slow, upright, open growth. L. (U.S. 2020 - Hulyn Smith).

name: Wenoing'S Summer Dream
description: (‘Xiameng Wenqing’ - Chinese Name). Bright Red. Medium to large, anemone to loose peony to semidouble form. Vigorous, upright, dense growth. Summer-Winter - Continuous. (C. azalea x Reticulata hybrid 'Dr. Clifford Parks’). (U.S. 2021 - Palm Landscape Architecture Co. Ltd., Guangzhou, Guangdong, China).

name: Yiao Huang Weizi
description: See ‘Yellow and Purple’

name: Zhanoqun Lady
description: (‘Da Qio’ - Chinese Name). Very Light Pink with slightly Deeper Pink on petal outer rim. Large to very large, rose form double to formal double with upstanding, separated, and mainly fluted petals. Vigorous growth. L. [(Reticulata hybrid ‘Suzanne Withers’ x ‘Nitidissima hybrid ‘Honeymoon’) x Japonica ‘Kona’]. (U.S. 2012 - John Wang, Orinda, CA).

name: Taiyo (The Sun)
description: Claret Rose with Yellow anthers and Creamy filaments. Small, single. Slow, upright growth; bloom has broad, overlapping petals, emarginate and slightly creped, with a compact stamen column; this snow Camellia cultivar has Light Yellow variegation along the midrib and the major veins of the Dark Green, glossy leaves. M-L. (Japan 1966 - Niigata Prefecture).

name: Kon
description: Japonica - Blackish Dark Red with Golden anthers and Pink filaments. Small, single cup shaped. M-L. (Japan 1937 - Hyégo Prefecture).
